{
  "body": "Reverse haze, diffused blur, soft focus, {{framing}} of {{subject}}.\n\n— Subject & atmosphere —\n{{subject}} The face is extremely attractive in a refined, ethereal way — not glamour, not cute — closer to renaissance angel meets contemporary cinematic anime heroine. The atmosphere is dreamy and elusive, as if the viewer is glimpsing a memory rather than a person.\n\n— Hair (the hero of the composition) —\n{{hair_motion}}. The hair carries the most visual energy in the frame — emphasize the chaotic beauty of flowing dynamic strands, with individual highlighted threads catching the light, some strands sweeping across the face and fading into the haze. Hair texture must remain physically believable: each strand has its own thickness, gloss falloff and translucency where light passes through.\n\n— Lighting —\n{{lighting}}. The light source carves volume on the face (forehead, nose bridge, cheekbone, jawline) with painterly chiaroscuro, then bleeds into the air via reverse haze, producing visible glowing bloom around the brightest areas. Subtle reflections and refractions shimmer on hair, eyes, and any glossy surfaces.\n\n— Background —\n{{background}}. Heavily blurred (deep bokeh), with soft light specks floating like dust motes in the haze. The background should suggest mood, not narrate scene — keep it abstract and atmospheric.\n\n— Color palette —\n{{color_palette}}, with high saturation in the highlights and gently desaturated shadows. Color must feel emotional — like the first frame of a film by Makoto Shinkai or the final shot of a Wong Kar-wai sequence.\n\n— Softness & rendering —\n{{softness_level}}. Glowing bloom blur diffusion is layered on the brightest highlights. Low noise, with a subtle film grain texture preserved over the entire image (medium-fine grain, not heavy). Rich texture details survive in the partially-sharp areas — eyelashes, iris pattern, lip surface, fabric weave.\n\n— Aesthetic direction —\nMinimalist composition, soft-focus aesthetics, emotional impressionism, avant-garde visual art aesthetics, cinematic luxury composition, masterpiece-level film aesthetics. Reference touch-points: Wong Kar-wai's saturated melancholy, Makoto Shinkai's lens flares and bloom, Pictorialist photography (Steichen, Käsebier), and Studio Ghibli's air-density treatment.\n\n— Composition & framing —\n{{framing}}. Captured in {{aspect_ratio}} aspect ratio. Negative space is filled with haze and bokeh, not emptiness — every region of the frame carries atmospheric information.\n\n— Rendering quality —\nCGI quality, Unreal Engine 5 rendering combined with Octane Render finishing, 8K master file, photorealistic skin subsurface scattering, hair card/strand hybrid technique with translucent tip lighting, volumetric atmosphere, raytraced bloom, cinematic color grade with film LUT.\n\n— Additional details —\n{{extra_notes}}\n\n— Strictly avoid —\n- Do NOT make the entire image uniformly blurry — softness must be artistic, with selective sharpness on eyes and key strands\n- Do NOT render plastic-doll skin — preserve subsurface scattering, faint pores, micro-translucency at the ears and nose tip\n- Do NOT use generic anime cel-shading — this is photorealistic CG with anime-inspired beauty, not anime style itself\n- Do NOT add lens dirt, scratches, heavy chromatic aberration, or fake-vintage filters\n- Do NOT crush the blacks — keep luminous information in the shadows\n- Do NOT add loud accessories, busy patterns, or jewelry that competes with the hair\n- Do NOT add text, watermark, logo, signature, or graphic overlay\n- Do NOT replicate any specific copyrighted character design literally — use the inspiration as mood/silhouette/palette only, with original facial features\n\nKeywords: dreamy portrait, soft focus, reverse haze, bloom diffusion, cinematic, Rembrandt lighting, ethereal, flowing hair, emotional impressionism, masterpiece, Unreal Engine 5, Octane render",
